Conflicts between the cytoverse and other packages

Source: R/conflicts.R
cytoverse_conflicts.Rd

This function lists all the conflicts between packages in the cytoverse and other packages that you have loaded.

cytoverse_conflicts()

Details

There are four conflicts that are deliberately ignored: intersect, union, setequal, and setdiff from dplyr. These functions make the base equivalents generic, so shouldn't negatively affect any existing code.

Examples

cytoverse_conflicts()
#> ── Conflicts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── cytoverse_conflicts() ──
#> ✖ ggcyto::%+%()               masks ggplot2::%+%()

#> ✖ flowCore::eval()            masks base::eval()
#> ✖ ncdfFlow::filter()          masks flowCore::filter(), stats::filter()
#> ✖ flowCore::head()            masks utils::head()
#> ✖ flowWorkspace::lapply()     masks ncdfFlow::lapply(), base::lapply()
#> ✖ flowCore::ls()              masks base::ls()
#> ✖ flowCore::ncol()            masks base::ncol()

#> ✖ ggcyto::print()             masks flowCore::print(), base::print()
#> ✖ ncdfFlow::split()           masks flowCore::split(), base::split()
#> ✖ flowCore::summary()         masks base::summary()
#> ✖ flowCore::tail()            masks utils::tail()
